31:### R001 — All user-facing M001 entry points require authentication before use across the proven local Web UI, CLI, registry/management, provider-backed chat, and smoke paths; Email and WhatsApp gateways are authenticated placeholder inspections only.
75:### R005 — The platform includes a Hermes-inspired general agent runtime skeleton for authenticated sessions, project-scoped chat interaction flow, provider-backed assistant responses, and observable planning/execution loop boundaries.
86:### R006 — The platform includes an authenticated, permission-checked tool registry and dispatcher skeleton boundary for inspecting placeholder tools without enabling real tool execution in M001.
97:### R007 — The platform includes an authenticated skill registry skeleton boundary for listing placeholder skills through defined platform and project-management surfaces without real skill invocation in M001.
